DURBAN - A municipal bus was torched as protests over land escalated in Bonela on Thursday. In recent days, the city's Land Invasion Unit has fought running battles with people who have attempted to build shacks on a vacant piece of land in Bonela. Tensions escalated on Thursday when a municipal bus was set alight on Vusi Mzimela (Bellair Road) at midday. An eyewitness said the bus was stopped by a mob of people and the driver forced out. It is alleged that bus was set alight because several shacks were demolished by the eThekwini land invasion unit. Land invaders have clashed with residents and ethekwini security guards for more than a week. The invaders want to occupy a piece of land along Wiggins and Blinkbonnie Roads.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
